SAP FI/CO Senior Business Analyst
SAP FI/CO Senior Business Analyst
Location:  Singapore
SAP FI/CO Senior Business Analyst – Permanent – Singapore
Amoria Bond is currently looking for a Senior SAP FI/CO Business Analyst for one of our major finance clients. The successful candidate will act a liaison between various business units, IT department and other departments
to clearly understand, analyze, and communicate the business needs throughout each step of the development process.
RESPONSIBILITIES
• Working with business, IT and vendors to identify opportunities for improvement in operations and processes, the analyst will get involved with the all the design / modification of underwriting and related systems;
• Interact with the business stakeholders and subject matter experts in order to understand their problems and needs; Gather, document, and analyze business requirements;
• Develops, clarifies and manages the scope of the project, defines contract deliverables and achieves targeted outcomes;
• Assembles project members with the department, identifies needed resources, assigns responsibilities and develops timeframes to facilitate successful completion of project activities and deliverables;
• Liaise with Finance users for reporting requirements and to improve finance processes to improve efficiency;
• Negotiate and effectively manage Finance SAP (FICO and BPC) work outsourced to external vendors to ensure timely and high quality deliverables;
• Manage Finance SAP user access requests to ensure that there is no conflict of interests and that assignment is correctly done;
• Maintain and provide support relating to Finance SAP systems to JVs and branches;
• Liaise with Internal and External auditors on Finance SAP systems queries;
• Review change requests and ensure proper requirement and technical documentation. Manage error logs and ensure timely resolution;
• Lead / Assist in the design of technical solutions; Document the functional and technical design of systems;
• Interact with architects and developers to ensure the system is properly implemented; Organise testing team to help test the system and create system documentation and user manuals;
• Lead / Assist in the design of testing and test data/cases;
• Define and manage project risk identification and mitigation process through interaction with project constituents and stakeholders.
• Identify on a timely basis all project barriers and identify strategies and approaches to overcome these barriers.
• Define and implement the appropriate change management strategy and plans to ensure that change management concerns are addressed during and after project implementation, as well as to ensure that the project impact is sustainable and supported by the business process owners.
• Communication and presentation (written and oral): above average communication skills with people from a wide variety of backgrounds; proficient in effective presentation techniques and with a good personal presence; proficient in receiving complex ideas with clarity and ensuring other staff understand these ideas
• Cross-functional and inter-disciplinary awareness: understanding the needs, objectives and constraints of those in other disciplines and functions
• Track record of identifying strengths and weaknesses and suggested areas of improvement.
• Solid requirements gathering and documentation skills – produces, reviews and edits requirements, specifications, business processes and recommendations related to proposed solution.
• Experience in developing functional specifications and system design specifications for client engagements
Please can all interested candidates forward a copy of their up-to-date CV to grahamcv@amoriabond.com for immediate interview.
Amoria Bond operates as an employment agency and employment business.
No terminology in this advert is intended to discriminate on the grounds of age, and we confirm that we are happy to accept applications from persons of any age for this role.
